{"id":"project-LICHEN-8h9c","title":"announce.rs: TLV parser stops on unknown type, missing subsequent valid fields","description":"File: rust/lichen-node/src/announce.rs:360-386

The parse_congestion TLV parser stops parsing on unknown types, potentially missing valid congestion data that follows:

```rust
fn parse_congestion(app_data: &[u8]) -> Option<u8> {
    let mut pos = 0;
    while pos + 1 < app_data.len() {
        let typ = app_data[pos];
        match typ {
            0x01 => { pos += 9; }   // GeoCoords
            0x02 => { return Some(app_data[pos + 1]); }  // Congestion
            _ => { return None; }   // Unknown type - STOPS PARSING
        }
    }
    None
}
```

If app_data contains [UnknownType, Congestion(0x02, value)], the parser gives up at the unknown type and never finds the congestion field.

Fix: TLV format should include length for unknown types to enable skip-over, or the parser should continue searching after unknown types.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:35:25.667836Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:35:25.667863Z"}

